{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Nnd4cTq1orR4e8GxPi1S58","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Tests for Slice A event types, envelope, and JSON Schema validation.\n2\t\n3\tCoverage targets:\n4\t\n5\t  - UUIDv7 generator produces well-formed IDs that survive\n6\t    ``is_well_formed_event_id`` and exhibit time-ordered prefixes.\n7\t  - Every active event type round-trips through ``Event.to_json``\n8\t    -> ``Event.from_json`` losslessly.\n9\t  - Each payload builder produces a payload that validates against\n10\t    the per-type JSON Schema; the combined event schema accepts a\n11\t    correct envelope+payload pair.\n12\t  - Negative cases: missing required envelope fields, wrong type,\n13\t    bad payload shape, unknown event type, additional payload\n14\t    fields, malformed event_id.\n15\t  - Reserved event types (threshold_crossed, plan_reauthored)\n16\t    validate too: Slice B writers can emit them now and have them\n17\t    survive the Slice A check.\n18\t  - design_reasoning_recorded REQUIRES linked_event_id (the Slice A\n19\t    tightening).\n20\t  - commit_landed accepts the change_class enum and the optional\n21\t    touched_paths field.\n22\t\"\"\"\n23\t\n24\tfrom __future__ import annotations\n25\t\n26\timport time\n27\tfrom itertools import pairwise\n28\tfrom typing import Any\n29\t\n30\timport pytest\n31\t\n32\tfrom bob_tools.ledger import (\n33\t    ACTIVE_EVENT_TYPES,\n34\t    RESERVED_EVENT_TYPES,\n35\t    SCHEMA_VERSION,\n36\t    AssumptionConfidence,\n37\t    CommitChangeClass,\n38\t    Event,\n39\t    EventSchemaError,\n40\t    EventType,\n41\t    GitSnapshot,\n42\t    RejectedApproach,\n43\t    is_well_formed_event_id,\n44\t    iter_validation_errors,\n45\t    validate_event,\n46\t    validate_event_id_format,\n47\t)\n48\tfrom bob_tools.ledger._uuid7 import uuid7\n49\tfrom bob_tools.ledger.events import (\n50\t    make_assumption_declared_payload,"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac94cef0-99df-4cb6-aede-46072f55262c","uuid":"459a26df-0fdd-4fe4-b8da-b8a45bc45bc4","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:42:48.918Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/mhcoen/proj/bob-tools/bob_tools/ledger/tests/test_events.py","content":"\"\"\"Tests for Slice A event types, envelope, and JSON Schema validation.\n\nCoverage targets:\n\n  - UUIDv7 generator produces well-formed IDs that survive\n    ``is_well_formed_event_id`` and exhibit time-ordered prefixes.\n  - Every active event type round-trips through ``Event.to_json``\n    -> ``Event.from_json`` losslessly.\n  - Each payload builder produces a payload that validates against\n    the per-type JSON Schema; the combined event schema accepts a\n    correct envelope+payload pair.\n  - Negative cases: missing required envelope fields, wrong type,\n    bad payload shape, unknown event type, additional payload\n    fields, malformed event_id.\n  - Reserved event types (threshold_crossed, plan_reauthored)\n    validate too: Slice B writers can emit them now and have them\n    survive the Slice A check.\n  - design_reasoning_recorded REQUIRES linked_event_id (the Slice A\n    tightening).\n  - commit_landed accepts the change_class enum and the optional\n    touched_paths field.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport time\nfrom itertools import pairwise\nfrom typing import Any\n\nimport pytest\n\nfrom bob_tools.ledger import (\n    ACTIVE_EVENT_TYPES,\n    RESERVED_EVENT_TYPES,\n    SCHEMA_VERSION,\n    AssumptionConfidence,\n    CommitChangeClass,\n    Event,\n    EventSchemaError,\n    EventType,\n    GitSnapshot,\n    RejectedApproach,\n    is_well_formed_event_id,\n    iter_validation_errors,\n    validate_event,\n    validate_event_id_format,\n)\nfrom bob_tools.ledger._uuid7 import uuid7\nfrom bob_tools.ledger.events import (\n    make_assumption_declared_payload,","numLines":50,"startLine":1,"totalLines":660}}}
